sentences: Sylvia Syms (December 2, 1917 – May 10, 1992) was an American jazz singer and actress.
As a teenager, she went to jazz nightclubs on New York's 52nd Street and received informal training from Billie Holiday.
Among others who observed her in nightclubs was Frank Sinatra who considered her the "world's greatest saloon singer."
She was signed to a contract by Decca Records, having her major success with a recording of "I Could Have Danced All Night" in 1956, which sold over one million copies and was awarded a gold disc.
